<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="376" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1194,1257]" pageId="3" pageNumber="376">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1194,1220]" pageId="3" pageNumber="376">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(after 
<bibRefCitation author="Fiege, D." box="[345,477,1195,1221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="376" pagination="440 - 455" refId="ref10078" refString="Fiege, D. (2019) Sternaspidae Carus, 1863 In: Purschke, G., Boggemann, M. &amp; Westheide, W. (Eds.), Handbook of Zoology. Annelida. Vol. I. Annelida Basal Groups and Pleistoannelida, Sedentaria I. De Gruyter, Berlin, pp. 440 - 455." type="book chapter" year="2019">Fiege 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Sternaspids with introvert hooks subdistally expanded. Preshield region with eight segments. Ventrocaudal shield stiff with poorly developed ribs and no concentric lines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
